ClusterFiles

groups articles into groups of articles.

Usage:
	./run --input DIR --k 50 --weighting tf --metric
		--input
			The directories containing text files to be classified, one directory per class
			
		--k
			The number of clusters into which articles are grouped.
		
		--weighting
			The term weighting function: tf, idf, or tfidf.
		
		--metric
			The distance metric: cosine, kl divergence, etc.
